info:
Brocade SAN content pack helps the user to better search, analyze and manage the log data generated by  Brocade SAN. Content pack can be used in two ways:
- Configure BNA to forward syslogs from all the switches of interest, to Log Insight
- Configure switches to forward syslog to Log Insight
name: Brocade - SAN
author: Brocade

info:
The UCS content pack contains critical information about everything within a UCS system from UCS Central and UCS Manager down to chassis, blades, and networking components. The content pack provides:

Component Faults and Reasons
When hardware issues are detected, quickly investigate and resolve them.

Configuration Changes and Faults
Quickly identify what configuration changes have occurred over time and get notification of configuration faults immediately.

Authentication Requests
Track user sessions from both the GUI and the CLI including failed log in attempts and authentication sources.

The UCS content pack is a powerful monitoring tool for UCS environments, making you aware of any issues quickly and allowing you to maintain a healthy environment at all times.
name: Cisco - UCS
author: Cisco Systems, Inc.

info:
The EMC VMAX content pack provides you with important information about your Symmetrix VMAX array(s) from sources such as Solutions Enabler and Unisphere for VMAX. The content pack enables:
 
Proactive monitoring of your VMAX array
Quickly identify issues using dashboards and pre-defined alerts.
 
Historical viewing of VMAX events
Using the custom date functionality view VMAX trends over extended periods of times to help identify potential problems before they impact production.
 
Additional information and context
Each dashboard widget includes information about the widget with links to documentation or any other information that might be applicable.
 
The EMC VMAX content pack will help bridge the gap between the VMware and system administrators, providing a common set of data by which the VMAX can be monitored and issues addressed.
name: EMC - VMAX
author: EMC Corporation

info: Import real-time network, web, database, storage, and memcache metrics into Log Insight that are otherwise difficult or impossible to log. To work, this app requires an ExtraHop appliance. You can download a free ExtraHop virtual appliance at http://www.extrahop.com/discovery
name: ExtraHop - Wire Data
author: ExtraHop Networks

info: The vCenter Log Insight General Content Pack provides generic information about any events being sent to your Log Insight instance. The information provided can be used to detect and investigate event anomalies. This Content Pack also includes Dashboard filters, a feature introduced in Log Insight 2.0, that allows for deeper analysis of Dashboard queries.
name: General
author: VMware, Inc.

info:
The content pack for Microsoft® Active Directory® provides you with information about key entities of any AD installation’s health using vCenter Log Insight’s ability to monitor Windows® Event Logs.  The content pack enables:
 
Accurate monitoring of your AD infrastructure
Focus on known problems through monitoring events raised in the Windows Event Log.
 
Key AD components are covered—AD security, AD DS, DFS, and DNS
Eight dashboards containing 37 widgets are included from AD security, AD DS, DFS, and DNS that go in depth to quantify your data in a multitude of manners to help diagnose problems in your AD infrastructure. 
 
Employs features added in Log Insight 2.0
Version 2.0 of Log Insight includes the ability to view logs posted to the Windows Event Log, which is pivotal to providing a minimally invasive AD log monitoring solution.  The dashboards feature widgets that showcase the slick new chart types for effortless visual consumption.
name: Microsoft - Active Directory
author: VMware, Inc.

info:

Employs features added in Log Insight 2.0

name: Microsoft - Exchange
author: VMware, Inc.

info:
The content pack for Microsoft® Windows® OS provides you with information about the fundamental elements of any Windows installation’s health through the use of the recently added feature to analyze events in the Windows Event Log.  The content pack enables:
 
Accurate monitoring of your Windows infrastructure
Focus on known problems through monitoring events raised in the Windows Event Log.
 
Essential Windows categories are covered—Application, System, and Security
Ten dashboards containing a total of 52 widgets are included from Application, System, and Security that go in depth to quantify your data in a multitude of manners to help diagnose problems in your infrastructure.
 
Employs features added in Log Insight 2.0
Version 2.0 of Log Insight included the ability to view logs posted to the Windows Event Log, which is pivotal to providing a minimally invasive Windows OS log monitoring solution.  The dashboards feature widgets that showcase the slick new chart types for effortless visual consumption.

author: Pure Storage

name: Synology DSM
author: VMware, Inc.

info: VMware® Horizon View™ (formerly VMware View) is a virtual desktop infrastructure solution that simplifies desktop management. This Content Pack simplifies managing View servers with analytic dashboards for Server, Sessions, Users, Domain and more by inspecting the Horizon View™ logs.
name: VMware - Horizon View
author: VMware, Inc.

info:
The vCAC content pack for Log Insight provides you with important information across all components of your vCAC environment and key dependencies such as vCenter Orchestrator and SSO. The content pack enables:

Proactive monitoring of your vCAC environment

Quickly identify issues and drill down to determine the root cause with powerful visualizations of your data and targeted queries.

Component-specific breakdown of vCAC events

Ability to analysis every component and every event dependencies to get a complete picture within an environment.

Troubleshooting and root-cause analysis

Specific queries to focus on the important events that indicate real problems with additional information and context to resolve detected issues quickly.
name: VMware - vCAC 6.0
author: VMware, Inc.

info: Content pack to analyze all the logs redirected from the vCenter Operations Manager instance. This content pack contains various dashboards, queries and alerts to provide better diagnostics and troubleshooting capabilities to the vCenter Operations Manager administrator. The dashboards are grouped in the major components of vCenter Operations Manager like Analytics, UI, Adapters etc. to provide better manageability. There are various alerts which can be enabled to get the alerts in vCenter Operations Manager as well as for sending emails to the administrator(s)
name: VMware - vCenter Operations Manager
author: VMware, Inc.

info:
This VMware vCloud Director (vCD) content pack provides you with information from vCD that will help you to have a more through understanding about the health and operational status of your private cloud. Using it you will provide you with:

Detailed vApp activity information: This content pack will give you visibility into what vApp operations are happening and when to show you load as well as usage trends.

Consolidated operational overview: Have a clear picture of the overall health of your vCD environment and find problematic areas that you did not know existed.

Robust alerting: Capitalize on an collection of alerts built by an experienced cloud team to help you quickly detect and respond to issues in your environment when something goes wrong.
name: VMware - vCloud Director
author: VMware, Inc.

info:
The vSphere content pack provides you with powerful insight into your vSphere logs, allowing you to make informed and proactive decisions within your environment. The content pack enables:

Proactive monitoring of your vSphere environment

• Quickly identify issues: The General - Problems dashboard gives you a single pane of glass to find problems in your vSphere environment.
• Drill down to determine the root cause: Dashboard filters make it easy to see logs from specific parts of your vSphere environment.
• Easily consume data: Powerful and dynamic visualizations make it possible to detect anomalies, perform trending analysis, and pinpoint specific issues through targeted queries.
• Alerts: Know what to monitor in your vSphere logs and get notified when such events are detected.

Track changes and isolate security threats

• Configuration management: Track user-initiated changes and automated vSphere actions via vCenter Server tasks
• Environmental changes: See what VMs are being moved through DRS and HA actions.
• Auditing: The General - Security dashboard allows you to find who is logging into vSphere devices from which locations and through what means.

Additional information and context

• Query notes: Each dashboard widget includes information about the widget with links to documentation, knowledge base articles, and any other information making it possible to understand the data presented.
• Inventory: The General - Inventory dashboard quantifies results seen through vSphere logs making it simple to ensure complete environment monitoring.
name: VMware - vSphere
author: VMware, Inc.
